  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6757.92 sitting right in the heart of massive negative gamma concentration (6745-6765 strikes all showing -5.8B to -7.2B), dealers are forced to sell into this decline and will continue amplifying any downward momentum until we clear these levels. The 50-65% GEX surge indicates rapid option flow changes, likely from put buying or call selling, which is expanding the negative gamma zone and forcing more dealer selling pressure. Key inflection points: break below 6745 could accelerate selling toward 6725 (GEX flip), while any bounce needs to reclaim 6765 to reduce dealer selling pressure, with 6800 acting as the major positive gamma magnet where dealers would flip to buying dips.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect continued downside pressure with dealers selling rallies until we clear the 6765-6745 negative gamma minefield.",
